<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-10T23:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-10T23:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51A/516: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-11T00:00:00-04:00">March 11,
                                    1942—midnight</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1034. Your no. 1050, March 5, 7 p.m. You should inform Sir Alexander
                            Cadogan that we have every desire to assist in the selection <pb facs="0239" n="227" xml:id="pg_227"/> of a financial adviser for
                            Iran. The concluding sentence of section 2 of your telegram under
                            reference reflects accurately the Department’s view of the matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>